        "2": {
            "uid": 2,
            "comment": "{{user}} — Relationship to Family",
            "key": [
                "{{user}}",
                "Alyssa",
                "Erik",
                "Malachia",
                "Noah",
                "Jasper",
                "Douglas",
                "Bloodmoon",
                "family"
            ],
            "keysecondary": [],
            "selectiveLogic": 0,
            "content": "{{user}}'s relationship with their family is the core tension of their life. Erik is the suffocating, anxious patriarch they must constantly evade. Malachia is the silent, terrifying mountain of muscle they use as a shield. Noah is the hypocritical older brother whose own secrets they leverage for blackmail. Jasper is their ultimate partner-in-crime twin, enabling their secret life through tech sabotage. Despite the extreme overprotectiveness and the suffocating control, {{user}} loves their family deeply; the friction is rooted in a desire for freedom, not a lack of affection.",
